title: Week 9: High school football capsules
text:
Week 9: High school football capsules Brian McCallum , FLORIDA TODAY 2:32 p.m. EDT October 22, 2015 Buy Photo Jalen Mitchell of Rockledge is taken down by Satellite players Andrew Abendroth (47) David Eaton (22) and Kyle Bassagnani (5) during last week’s game in Satellite Beach. (Photo: Craig Bailey/FLORIDA TODAY) Buy Photo 
Astronaut (4-3, 3-0) at Cocoa (5-2, 2-0) 
7 p.m. 
Last week: The War Eagles won at Lake Highland Prep, 18-12. The Tigers won a Thursday game at Orlando Jones, 63-6. 
Game notes: District 5-4A game. Cocoa, No. 4 in this week’s Class 4A poll, has won the last five between these two. Astronaut last won in 2007, 14-10 in Titusville. 
Palm Bay (6-1, 3-0) at Merritt Island (5-2, 3-0) 
7 
Last week: Both teams played Thursday. The Pirates won, 49-14 over Space Coast, and the Mustangs defeated Titusville, 33-0. 
Game notes: District 14-5A game. Class 5A No. 10 Palm Bay has not lost since the season opener, while the Mustangs, among teams receiving votes in this week’s rankings, have won four in a row. 
Okeechobee (3-4, 1-2) at Eau Gallie (4-3, 1-2) 
7 
Last week: The Brahmans defeated Bayside in 5 OTs, 65-58, while the Commodores lost at Jensen Beach, 36-29. 
Game notes: District 14-6A game. This is the final home game for Eau Gallie in the regular season. 
Heritage (6-1, 3-0) at Jensen Beach (3-3, 2-1) 
7 
Last week: The Panthers beat Sebastian River, 28-15. The Falcons defeated Eau Gallie, 36-29. 
Game notes: District 14-6A game. Heritage has won both games between the teams, 44-10 in 2013 in Palm Bay, 34-7 at Jensen Beach last year. 
Titusville (2-5, 1-2) at Rockledge (4-3, 1-2) 
7 
Last week: The Terriers lost a Thursday night game to Merritt Island, 33-0. The Raiders won at Satellite on Friday, 47-14. 
Game notes: District 14-5A. The home team has won the last three games in this series. Rockledge had the last road win, 30-0 in 2011. 
Space Coast (4-2, 1-2) at Satellite (1-5, 0-3) 
7 
Last week: The Vipers lost on Thursday at Palm Bay, 49-14. The Scorps lost on Friday to Rockledge, 47-14. 
Game notes: District 14-5A game. Satellite won the last meeting, in 2012, breaking a seven-win Space Coast streak in the series. 
Melbourne (0-7) at Bayside (0-7) 
7 
Last week: The Bulldogs led early but lost at South Fork, 35-21. The Bears lost in five overtimes in Okeechobee, 65-58. 
Game notes: Melbourne has won the last two in this series and three of the last four. 
Holy Trinity (6-1) at Lake Highland Prep (5-2) 
7:30 
Last week: The Tigers defeated Archbishop Curley, 48-13. The Highlanders lost to Astronaut, 18-12. 
Game notes: Holy Trinity will play for the District 6-3A title next week against John Caroll, in a game in Melbourne. 
Cocoa Beach (1-6) at Father Lopez (3-4) 
7 
Last week: The Minutemen were off but lost their last game, 35-0 at Eau Gallie on Oct. 9. The Green Wave lost at Ocala Trinity Catholic, 55-13. 
Game notes: Father Lopez opened the season with a 49-20 loss at Melbourne Central Catholic. Cocoa Beach lost to the Hustlers three weeks ago at home, 47-8. 
Santa Fe Catholic (7-0) at Merritt Island Christian (3-4) 
7 
Last week: The Hawks won at All Saints Academy, 41-6. The Cougars lost at Lake Mary Prep, 14-8. 
Game notes: Santa Fe has scored 35 or more points five times. MIC has scored more than 50 twice.
